Race.SpecificTitle: PW Prop. (Medical and Health Facilities) -- .96 Mills Rededication - PC - 10 Yrs.
Race.FullText: Shall the Parish of St. John the Baptist, State of Louisiana (the "Parish"), which is currently levying a special tax of ninety-six hundredths (.96) mills (the "Tax") on all property subject to taxation in the Parish (an estimated $380,000 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the Tax for an entire year), through the year 2027 for public health units in the Parish pursuant to an election held in the Parish on April 9, 2016, be authorized to rededicate the proceeds of the Tax heretofore or hereafter received for the purpose of maintaining, operating and improving medical and public health facilities and services in the Parish?
